DUAL table is present in every Oracle database.
It contains only one column - DUMMY, datatype - VARCHAR2(1).
It contains only one row - value in DUMMY of 'X'

Purpose of DUAL - to run a SELECT statement to get some other task acomplished, 
such as obtaining the output of a function.

Example: Oracle function SYSDATE - displaying current date according to the OSof the server on which Oracle DB is installed

SELECT SYSDATE FROM DUAL;
